cicognara-rails.title: Troubleshoot item count from contributing institutions

comments.body:
The issue seems to be fixed by re-running `rake tei:index` on the production server. 

I also noticed that there was no `cicognara.tei.xml` file in the production server before I ran the `rake tei:index` task. Below are the steps that I ran on the server:

```
# No cicognara.tei.xml file 
deploy@cicognara1:/opt/cicognara/current$ ls public/
422.html  assets  cicognara.marc.xml  favicon.ico  robots.txt

# Download the catalogo files (cicognara.mrx.xml  cicognara.tei.xml )
deploy@cicognara1:/opt/cicognara/current$ TEIPATH=public/cicognara.tei.xml MARCPATH=public/cicognara.mrx.xml bundle exec rake tei:catalogo:update

# Confirm files are on disk.
deploy@cicognara1:/opt/cicognara/current$ ls public/
422.html  assets  cicognara.marc.xml  cicognara.mrx.xml  cicognara.tei.xml  favicon.ico  robots.txt


# Reindex
deploy@cicognara1:/opt/cicognara/current$ TEIPATH=public/cicognara.tei.xml MARCPATH=public/cicognara.mrx.xml bundle exec rake tei:index
```

I can confirm that running `rake getty:import` sets `contributing_library_facet` facet counts back to the wrong numbers. Tested on my local environment with the latest version of the code.

Re-running `rake tei:index` sets the numbers back to the correct values. I am still not sure *why* this happen, but that seems to be what happened on this particular case.

A quick fix will be to update the crontab to run `rake tei:index` after `rake getty:import` but we will need to make sure we download the files via `rake tei:catalogo:update` before the index task is run.

@carolyncole I looked at your comment closer after the meeting and what you are saying is correct.

Moderator:
- may be assigned to one or more collections (For example: Hannah is assigned to all collections, but Neggin might only be assigned to the main Research Data collection, and Chun might only be assigned to all PPPL collections.)
- may add users (depositors) to submit data
- may add users (additional moderators) to a collection they are assigned to, but not to other collections
- may assign themselves and other moderators from the same collection as a "curator" of a deposit
- signage next to name (number 1 in screenshot above) indicates "Moderator"

Curator:
- the moderator when assigned to a submission
- ID or name shows in "Curator" column (number 2 in screenshot above)

Please let me know if we need further clarification on these details.
